Q2ï¸âƒ£ Data Protection Create a class BankAccount: private variable balance method deposit(int amt) method withdraw(int amt) balance should not go negative

Q2ï¸âƒ£ Data Protection

Goal: Prevent invalid balance update (NO direct setter)

class BankAccount {

    // Step 1: Private balance (sensitive data)
    private int balance = 1000;

    // Step 2: Deposit method
    public void deposit(int amt) {
        if (amt > 0) {
            balance += amt;
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Withdraw with validation
    public void withdraw(int amt) {
        if (amt > 0 && amt <= balance) {
            balance -= amt;
        } else {
            System.out.println("Insufficient balance");
        }
    }

    // Step 4: Getter (optional, read-only)
    public int getBalance() {
        return balance;
    }
}

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        BankAccount acc = new BankAccount();
        acc.deposit(500);
        acc.withdraw(300);
        acc.withdraw(2000);

        System.out.println("Balance: " + acc.getBalance());
    }
}


ðŸ§  Interview line:

For sensitive data, we avoid setters and expose behavior methods.
